17/12/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Solomon Passy serves as chairman of the UN Security Council's open meeting on Kosovo Wednesday (17 December). 
In New York, he is also scheduled to meet with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan. 
The Security Council meeting is organised by the presidency of the Council, held by Bulgaria this month. 
Last week, the Council supported a set of written standards to prepare UN-administered Kosovo for final status, including free, fair and regular elections, free media and a sound and impartial legal system. 
(BTA, Foreign Ministry press release - 16/12/03)
